Francisco Queiroz said this included $3 billion siphoned off from the sovereign wealth fund. He said some countries were obstructing Angola's efforts to track down the looted funds. The son of Angola's former President José Eduardo dos Santos, who headed the sovereign wealth fund, is on trial for corruption. 

José Filomeno dos Santos denies the charges. Angolan President João Lourenço has vowed to crack down on the country's massive corruption problem.
--BBC--